President Muhammadu Buhari has inaugurated the governing board of the newly established North East Development Commission (NEDC). The commission is to fast track the rebuilding of the region which has devasted by insecurity especially the insurgents perpetrated by suspected members of the Boko Haram sect. Major General (rtd) Paul Tarfa, chairs the board of the commission. Other members of the board are Mohammed Alkali, Managing Director of the NEDC; Musa Yashi, Executive Director, Humanitarian Affairs; Muhammed Jawa, Executive Director, Administration and Finance; and Omar Mohammed, Executive Director, Operations. Others are David Kente, member representing North East Zone; Asmau Mohammed, member representing North West Zone; Benjamin Adanyi, member representing North Central Zone, Olawale Oshun, member representing South West Zone; Dr. T. Ekechi, member representing South East; and Obasuke McDonald,  member representing South-South. President Buhari while inaugurating the board at the council chambers of the presidential villa, Abuja shortly before the commitment of the Federal Executive Council (FEC) meeting said Inaugurating the board, said the establishment of the commission was in fulfilment of the pledge of his administration and part of the strategy to rebuild the zone. He said the establishment was also in appreciation of the massive electoral support of the zone in 2015 and 2019 general elections. For the successful take-off of the commission, the president said N10billion was provided in this yearâ€™s budget, urging the board to use the fund judiciously. The President mandated the board to conduct a comprehensive survey of all the states in the northeast to know the magnitude of the damage caused by the insurgency.